headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 25 points, and Karl-Anthony Towns added 21 points and 14 rebounds and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Detroit Pistons 128-117 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Towns lead Timberwolves past Pistons, 128-117

events.name: Miami Heat at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 24 points, Bam Adebayo added 18 points and 11 rebounds and the Miami Heat dominated the short-handed San Antonio Spurs 112-95 on Thursday night in Kyle Lowry’s return.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro, Heat dominate short-handed Spurs 112-95 to end skid

headlines.description: — There was no way a sore shoulder was going to prevent Trae Young from playing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young has 43 points, Hawks end Suns' 11-game winning streak

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 25 points and 13 rebounds, Chris Boucher added 16 points and 10 rebounds, and the Toronto Raptors beat the Chicago Bulls 127-120 in overtime on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 25 points as Raptors beat Bulls 127-120 in OT

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson took a flick pass from Stephen Curry in transition then drove hard past Davion Mitchell to the left corner and unleashed an off-balanced baseline 3-pointer that was spot on, raising an arm high to celebrate.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson dazzles from deep, Warriors beat Kings 126-114

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson isn't fazed by Los Angeles Clippers games coming down to the wire, especially against their arena co-tenants.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's layup propels Clippers to 111-110 win over Lakers
